subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.

Metajalysus clavatus

(
Figs. 1–3
) is distinguished by the general brown color, the high middle tubercle and short, round lateral tubercles on the pronotum (
Fig. 13
), the long dense setae on the pronotal disc, the relatively short antennae and legs, with a shorter scape and femora, the clavate femora with distinct setigerous tubercles giving a bumpy appearance, and the inverted V-shaped ventral margin of the male genital aperture (
Figs. 17–19
).
